    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I've done the easy part of this in pull request #275. The hard part is what to do about account storage. Storage is a trie (which is mutable) that is currently stored in the immutable `Account` class.\r\n\r\nThe two possible solutions are:\r\n1. Turn `storage` into `storage_root`, store the storage trie somewhere else and require updates the storage trie to update `storage_root` in `Account`.\r\n2. Remove the `storage` from `Account` entirely and require callers to `encode_account()` to provide the `storage_root`.\r\n\r\nI'm mildly in favour of approach 2. Mostly because the verkle trie proposal will move (most of) account storage out of the `Account` object and into the main trie, so code shouldn't rely on `storage` being in `Account` for future proofing. Also being forced to recalculate the storage root every time storage changes seems annoying and inefficient.",
